---
layout: layouts/base.njk
title: English Home
description: English entry point for the research workflow guidebook.
lang: en
activeSection: home
langSwitch:
  url: /ko/
  label: 한국어
pageClass: page-home
---
<main class="content-shell">
  {% include "components/left-rail.njk" %}

  <article class="doc-content panel" data-pagefind-body>
    <section class="doc-hero doc-hero-simple">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">English Guidebook</p>
        <h1>Research workflow guides for setup, writing, and GitHub collaboration.</h1>
        <p class="lead">
          Use this guide to reach a working local setup, settle into a repeatable writing loop, and move into calm repository collaboration.
        </p>
        <p class="subtle">
          Start with Start Here if you are beginning from zero. If your environment is already working, use the left rail to jump straight to the section you need.
        </p>
        <div class="button-row">
          <a class="button button-primary" href="/en/start-here/">Start with Start Here</a>
          <a class="text-link" href="/">Back to language landing</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="doc-section">
      <h2>How to use this guide</h2>
      <div class="stack-list">
        <article class="stack-item">
          <h3>Get one project compiling first</h3>
          <p>Start with the shortest path to a working toolchain before you worry about convenience features.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="stack-item">
          <h3>Then turn it into a daily workflow</h3>
          <p>Move from setup into writing, preview, and GitHub habits that hold up during real research work.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="doc-section">
      <h2>Sections</h2>
      <div class="feature-grid">
        {% for section in navigation.sections %}
          <a class="feature-card panel" href="{{ section.url.en }}">
            <p class="card-kicker">{{ section.kicker.en }}</p>
            <h3>{{ section.title.en }}</h3>
            <p>{{ section.summary.en }}</p>
          </a>
        {% endfor %}
      </div>
    </section>
  </article>
</main>
